title: For Trade:  Mosin Nagant M44 Tula
location: Near CSU Campus, Fort Collins, Colorado
postcontent: The Mosin Nagant M44 from Tula is considered to be one of the more rare and higher quality models of the Mosin Nagant. Less than 100,000 of the M44 were made in Tula and production of this model only took place in the year 1944. Even less of the Tula made M44s were issued to the military, however this rifle has markings indicating that it was issued as military ordinance. Tula is well known for being an arsenal that produces high quality arms, reports state that the machinery used was of higher quality and that the workers were more precise when constructing arms. If you are a Mosin Nagant enthusiast, this is a rare gem and, at the risk of sounding like too much of a commercial salesman, a must have. Athough the stock could use a refinish, this is nevertheless a very high quality and rare Mosin Nagant. I've loved this rifle since I first held it, however it may be worth trading for a semi automatic just due to preference. Other than that, I would never part with this rifle. I will also throw in 20 stripper clips, 400 rounds of steel core ammunition, 20 rounds of lead tipped ammunition, and an ammo box. This should all come out to be worth at least $420 value, $300 for the rifle and $120 for the ammunition, ammo box is free! I am open to negotiation among the trade as, shoot me an email and I'll get back to you as soon as possible. I will send pictures... Had too much trouble with armslist posting them.
